<h3>Stay in a Houseboat</h3>
<p>Enjoy the famous backwaters of Kerala that network throughout Kerala. Houseboat cruising is a great way to witness the beauty of the Kerala countryside and explore the local way of life. Book Kerala tour packages with invisit to get exciting deals on Kerala packages.</p>

<h3>River Rafting in Kerala</h3>
<p>River rafting in Kerala is one of a memsmric experience to have during Kerala trip. Tackle the speed of Tejjaswini river and enjoy the gentle flow of Wayanad. Book Kerala tour packages with invisit to enjoy thrilling River rafting in Kerala.</p>

<h3>Visit Munnar's Tea Estates and Gardens</h3>
<p>Munnar is one of the most beautiful hill stations in Kerala and is famous for its sprawling tea plantations, scenic water falls, and cool climate. Learn about tea cultivation and production in Munnar with invisit&rsquo;s Kerala tour packages.</p>

<h3>Train Ride Through Kerala</h3>
<p>A train ride is one of the top things to do in Kerala as the Ernakulam-Kollam-Trivandrum route through Kerala offers stunning sights throughout the journey. While in Kerala don&rsquo;t miss out on enjoying these scenic views on your train journey.</p>

<h3>Relax With an Ayurvedic Treatment</h3>
<p>Enjoy a traditional spa treatment with an infusion of ayurvedic medicines and techniques to heal your inner soul. The session includes Abhyanga, Shirodhara, Nasya etc treatments.</p>

<h3>Witness Kathakali Performance</h3>
<p>Kerala is the heartland of Kathakali, an amazing dance form that perfectly blends dance, drama, and music. Witness the expressive and powerful dance performances of Kathakali with our Kerala travel packages.</p>

<h3>Watch a Snake Boat Race</h3>
<p>Vallam Kali, or snake boat race, is the traditional boat race in Kerala. The race is mainly performed during the harvest festival of Onam, which falls in the spring. Enjoy the Snake Boat Race with invisit&rsquo;s Kerala tour packages.</p>

<h3>Must Try Foods in Kerala</h3>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Sadhya</strong>: A traditional vegetarian feast served on a banana leaf, Sadhya is a culinary experience not to be missed.</li>
  <li><strong>Puttu and Kadala Curry</strong>: Puttu is a steamed rice cake made with grated coconut, while Kadala curry is a black chickpea curry.</li>
  <li><strong>Appam with Stew</strong>: Appam is a fermented pancake made with rice flour and coconut milk. It is usually served with a vegetable stew or curry.</li>
  <li><strong>Parotta and Ilaneer</strong>: Malabar Parotta is a flaky, layered flatbread that is a staple in Kerala. It is often served with a variety of curries or stews, or enjoyed with Ilaneer, which is fresh coconut water.</li>
  <li><strong>Kappa and Meen Curry</strong>: Kappa is boiled tapioca, and Meen Curry is fish curry. This is a classic Kerala dish that is both comforting and flavorful.</li>
  <li><strong>Erachi Petti</strong>: Erachi Petti is a deep-fried dish made with mutton or chicken. The meat is marinated in a mixture of spices and then deep-fried until crispy.</li>
  <li><strong>Palada Payasam</strong>: Palada Payasam is a sweet rice pudding made with milk, rice, jaggery, and nuts.</li>
  <li><strong>Banana Fritters (Pazham Pori):</strong> Banana Fritters, also known as Pazham Pori, are a popular snack food in Kerala.</li>
  <li><strong>Kerala Porotta:</strong> Kerala Porotta is a layered flatbread that is similar to Malabar Parotta, but it is made with maida flour instead of wheat flour.</li>
</ul>

